-- 6. Zed
('zed', 'Zed', 'High-performance AI-native code editor built in Rust for professional developers',
'Zed is a next-generation code editor built from scratch in Rust, designed for performance and collaboration, with AI deeply integrated rather than bolted on. The editor loads and responds faster than Electron-based alternatives like VS Code, which matters for large codebases where editor lag reduces flow. Zed''s AI features include an inline assistant that transforms selected code, a full chat panel powered by Anthropic''s Claude and other models, and context-aware completions. The editor supports real-time collaborative editing - multiple developers can share a session and code together in real time, similar to Google Docs for code, with zero configuration required. Zed is open-source with a free personal tier and a paid Pro plan at $10 per month that includes additional AI credits beyond the free monthly allocation. The editor targets professional developers and teams who prioritise performance and want a modern alternative to VS Code without switching to a fully AI-controlled environment like Cursor. Zed is available on macOS and Linux, with Windows support in development. Extension support is actively growing and the editor is approaching VS Code parity for common language server and debugging workflows.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=zed.dev&sz=64',
'https://zed.dev', 'https://zed.dev',
