-- 7. Supermaven
('supermaven', 'Supermaven', 'Ultra-fast AI code completion with a 1 million token context window',
'Supermaven is an AI code completion tool engineered for speed and context length. The system uses a proprietary architecture that delivers completions faster than other AI coding assistants while supporting a 1 million token context window - large enough to include an entire large codebase as context for more relevant completions. Where other completions tools understand a few files at once, Supermaven can reference hundreds of files when generating suggestions, surfacing completions that reflect patterns from across the project rather than just the immediate code. The tool integrates with VS Code and JetBrains editors through plugins. Supermaven was founded by Jacob Jackson, the original creator of Tabnine, and focuses on code completion rather than building a comprehensive chat-based coding assistant. The free tier includes basic completions with limited context. The Pro plan at $10 per month unlocks the full 1 million token context window and priority model access. Supermaven is particularly popular among developers who find existing completions tools too slow or too narrow in context, producing suggestions that feel disconnected from the broader codebase architecture.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=supermaven.com&sz=64',
'https://supermaven.com', 'https://supermaven.com',
