-- 8. Aider
('aider', 'Aider', 'AI pair programmer for terminal-based development with full git integration',
'Aider is an open-source AI pair programming tool that runs in the terminal and integrates directly with git. The workflow is distinct from editor plugins: you start a session in your project directory, add relevant files to the context, describe what you want to change in plain English, and Aider applies the changes as git commits with descriptive messages. This approach keeps every AI-generated change tracked in version history, making it easy to review, revert, or understand what was changed and why. Aider supports Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and many other models through API, and works with any codebase in any language. It is particularly strong at multi-file refactoring tasks where changes need to be consistent across many files simultaneously - Aider maps dependencies and applies coordinated changes rather than requiring the developer to edit each file individually. Aider benchmarks highly on coding tasks compared to other AI coding tools and has an active open-source community contributing improvements. The tool itself is free under an Apache 2.0 license. API costs for the connected LLM apply separately, with Claude typically being the recommended model for complex tasks.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=aider.chat&sz=64',
'https://aider.chat', 'https://aider.chat',
